# Verify Before Answering

Never answer questions about how the codebase works from memory or assumption. Always read the relevant file first.

- If asked how a feature works, read the file before responding.
- If asked whether something exists (a modal, a handler, a check), search or read the code to confirm before saying yes or no.
- Stating something as fact without verifying it first is not acceptable, even if it seems obvious.
- If you are challenged on an answer, do not defend it — read the code immediately and correct yourself if wrong.

A wrong answer stated confidently is worse than saying "let me check."
